# Prisma migration policy (HARD RULES)

When working anywhere inside `backend-simple-reserva/prisma/` you MUST follow these rules. They are non-negotiable.

## Forbidden

- `prisma db push` is NEVER allowed. Not for prototyping, not for "just this once", not even with `--accept-data-loss`. Do not suggest it, do not run it, do not document it as an option.
- Do NOT hand-edit files inside `prisma/migrations/<timestamp>_*/migration.sql` after the migration has been committed. Create a new migration instead.
- Do NOT delete or rename existing migration folders unless the user explicitly asks for a squash/reset.

## Required workflow for ANY schema change

1. Edit `prisma/schema.prisma`.
2. Run `npx prisma migrate dev --name <short_snake_case_description>` against your local dev DB.
3. Verify with `npx prisma migrate status` and `npx prisma validate`.
4. Commit BOTH the `schema.prisma` change AND the new `prisma/migrations/<timestamp>_<name>/` folder in the same commit.
5. Production deploys apply changes via `npx prisma migrate deploy` only — never `db push`.

## If migrate dev fails

- Read the error. Fix the schema or write a custom migration via `npx prisma migrate dev --create-only --name <name>` and edit the generated SQL before re-running `migrate dev`.
- If you truly need to wipe local dev DB: `npx prisma migrate reset` (local only, asks for confirmation). Never run reset against any non-local `DATABASE_URL`.
